 der Lösungen ist in einheitlich und maßstäblich neu gezeichneten Grundrissen und Schnitten aufgearbeitet.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aArchitecture / Design. 0aArchitecturexDesign. 0aArchitecture. 4aArchitektur. 4aBautypologie. 4aHausbau. 4aWohnungsbau. 7aARCHITECTURE / Buildings / Public, Commercial & Industrial.2bisacsh1 aBrauneck, Per, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET KUNST UND ARCHITEKTUR 2009z9783110318883oZDB-23-DKA0 cprintz978303460072940uhttps://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-0346-0442-040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783034604420423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783034604420/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2009  aZDB-23-DKAb2009  aZDB-23-GAAc2000d2014